Notes-Module 2 What is a Market?
What is a Market?

It is defined as " a regular gathering of people for the purpose and sale of provisions, livestock, and other commodities."

I believe it is an exchange for something with money or services. Its when parties engage in exchanging or trading.

In Economics, a market is one of a variety of systems used whereby parties engage in some sort of exchange.

